# Outlook Rules Manager - Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env in the project root (or .env.{profile} for multi-account)
#
# SECURITY: This file and all .env* files are gitignored.
# Never commit files containing real Client/Tenant IDs.
# Azure AD Application Registration
# Get these from Azure Portal > Microsoft Entra ID > App registrations > Your App
ClientId="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
TenantId="00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
# Optional: Friendly name for this profile (used in logging)
ProfileName="Default"
# =======================
# MULTI-ACCOUNT SETUP
# =======================
# To manage multiple email accounts (e.g., personal + work):
#
# 1. Create profile-specific .env files:
#    .env.personal  -> For personal Microsoft/Outlook account
#    .env.work      -> For work/corporate Microsoft 365 account
#    .env.demo      -> For demo/test tenant
#
# 2. Create profile-specific rules configs (optional):
#    rules-config.personal.json  -> Personal email rules
#    rules-config.work.json      -> Work email rules
#
# 3. Use the -ConfigProfile parameter when running scripts:
#    .\Connect-OutlookRulesApp.ps1 -ConfigProfile personal
#    .\Manage-OutlookRules.ps1 -Operation List -ConfigProfile personal
#
# Each profile requires its own Azure AD app registration in its respective tenant.
# Personal accounts use your personal Microsoft tenant (or create one at portal.azure.com).
# Work accounts use your organization's Microsoft 365 tenant.